      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>3-Methyl-2-butanol has five signals in its <sup>13</sup>C NMR spectrum at 17.90, 18.15, 20.00, 35.05, and 72.75 <i>δ.</i> Why are the two methyl groups attached to C3 nonequivalent? Making a molecular model should be helpful.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbmdVIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--236bd4e08de266798f4fddeeef595d76df58bf20/OChem_13_EC_025.jpg\" alt=\"The structure of 2-methyl-2-butanol with main chain carbons numbered 1 through 4.\">",
